## Code Style & Best Practices

### TypeScript
- Always use strict typing, avoid `any` where possible
- Create interfaces in `src/types/` for API responses
- Use discriminated unions for complex data structures

### React Components
- Use functional components with hooks (no class components)
- Place data fetching in `useEffect`
- Separate concerns: fetching, filtering, rendering
- Add loading and error states for all async operations

### Naming Conventions
- Files: kebab-case (e.g., `fetch-pools.tsx`)
- Components: PascalCase (e.g., `FetchPools`)
- Functions/variables: camelCase
- Constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE

### Performance
- Component memoization via React.FC when beneficial
- Avoid unnecessary re-renders
- Cache API responses server-side (1-hour fresh TTL, 2-hour stale fallback)

